.TH "pci_epc_clear_bar" 9 "pci_epc_clear_bar" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_epc_clear_bar \- reset the BAR
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pci_epc_clear_bar
.BI "(struct pci_epc *epc "  ","
.BI "u8 func_no "  ","
.BI "struct pci_epf_bar *epf_bar "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "epc" 12
the EPC device for which the BAR has to be cleared
.IP "func_no" 12
the endpoint function number in the EPC device
.IP "epf_bar" 12
the struct epf_bar that contains the BAR information
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Invoke to reset the BAR of the endpoint device.
